  "texts": [
    "In both cases, the simulations were run for several hours of solar time to achieve a stationary regime, after which we took snapshots every 10 s of solar time during 1 solar hour.",
    "The magnetic field divergence was computed from those snapshots in the stationary regime.",
    "An example of this computation is given in Figures 5 and 6.",
    "The upper panels of Figure 5 reveal a typical network-like pattern of magnetic structures coinciding with intergranular lanes at the solar surface, with a mean unsigned strength, |B|, around 120 G at the photospheric base in the SSD case and 160 G in the B Z = 50 G case.",
    "The individual magnetic field concentrations are, however, much stronger in the B Z = 50 G, reaching 2 kG."
